s are tighter in star-forming regions, the nonthermal emission is\ncorrelated also with the more quiescent molecular gas in the ISM. An almost\nlinear molecular star-formation law exists in M 33 when excluding diffuse\nstructures. Massive star formation amplifies the magnetic field and increases\nthe number of high-energy cosmic ray electrons, which can help the onset of\nwinds and outflows.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Sep 2022 10:13:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-07"}
